      "commit_id": null,
      "commit_url": null,
      "created_at": "2026-04-28T12:27:45Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-04-28T12:27:45Z",
      "author_association": "MEMBER",
      "body": "The difference with `send` and the other RPC calls you mention is that `send` does actually create and broadcast the transaction at the moment, so the anti-fee sniping makes sense.\n\nIn the other cases the user or the software using the RPC should set the locktime to the height they want in case they want to use anti-fee snipping. Because the time of the creation of the transaction is likely not going to be the broadcast time.\n\nRegarding privacy, if we set anti-fee sniping for other transactions than just the ones created with `send` they will be easily finger-printable as Core Wallet transactions because it would be the only wallet setting the anti-fee sniping for those.",
      "user": {
        "login": "polespinasa",
        "id": 57642229,
        "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjU3NjQyMjI5",
